abstract: The iron ship Susser, from Mobile, for Liverpool, was towed into Tybec last night. On the 27th inst. fire was discovered in her hold amidships. The hatches were immediately closed, and ventilation shut off. An examination was made to-day by the Surveyor, and the ship ordered to be towed to safe anchorage off Venus Point for a further investigation, which will be held to-morrow.
